Akwa Ibom State Government has warned property owners and developers in the state against constructing illegal structures along with ongoing road project sites. Speaking through the  State Commissioner for Works and Fire Service, Prof Eno Ibanga during road project Inspection and Demolition of illegal structures in Uyo on Wednesday, the government said such acts were obstructing ongoing road work on the expansion of Airport road, along Mbiabong axis in Uyo. Prof Ibanga assured that both rightful property owners who had received compensation and owners of illegal structures were given adequate time to evacuate their belongings before the demolition exercise. NSCDC Commandant Advocates Security Training For Pupils In Ondo Bayelsa Assembly Wants Probe Of Moribund State-Owned Motel “Government will not waste time in future  to wait for recalcitrant landlords who have collected compensation for their property but refuse  to evacuate their belongings from the building,” he said Our Correspondent gathered that the demolition exercise was carried out after payment of compensations to owners of affected property by the state government,  while notice to vacate, to enable uninterrupted work on the road project was duly served on them. It was also noted that some of the affected structures were newly erected after work on the expansion project had commenced and demolition carried out on other surrounding structures. The Commissioner, therefore, used to issue a strict warning to developers against the construction of illegal structures on government right of way, adding  that defaulters may not receive such soft treatment in the future.